\pard\plain \fi720\sl288\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Death is a terr}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 ifying}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  thing, but Life is }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 more so. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Life kills. Life kills, and it eats what it kills, and for some reason, people fear death. As any well-studied Solitant student can see, do not fear death, fear life! }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 There is a tribe in the Baree lowlands, the Ferzamun, who will not take shade under tree or bush because they believe that bark-fleshed leafy beings survive in the desert by poisoning the air to kill whatever sits underneath. A man falls asleep in that shade, he dies, and his body\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s water will sustain the plant for years. His bones, once buried, will fertilize the soil for the next generation.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Living things kill. Living things kill and eat each other. It is believed}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 , by those who seek out demons,}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  that this self-perpetuating cycle is motivated by the Spark\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s desire to be reunite with itself.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Elrahet was no Solitant, and yet she prayed the Solitant\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s prayer as she sliced open Ayram\u8217\'92s wrist and sipped his flesh.}
